notesStmt.note: 2nd and 3rd works published at Dillingen by Johannes Mayer.

msContents.summary: Commentary on Aristotle's Physics by the Jesuit Christoph Brandis, professor at Dillingen, taken down by his student Joannes Huober. (Compare Huober's condensed version of this commentary found in UPenn Ms. Codex 779.) Bound together with two printed pamphlets on Aristotle.

msItem.title: Commentarius in octo libros physicorum Aristotelis peripatetici
msItem.author: Brandis, Christoph
Enzenmiller, Johannes
Pfiffer, Adelricus

supportDesc.extent: 493 leaves : 197 x 157 (166 x 110) mm. bound to 212 x 160 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii (contemporary paper) + 493 + i (contemporary paper); [ii],1-941, [942-984]; contemporary pagination in ink, modern pagination in pencil, upper outer corners. 5 blank leaves, separate printed pagination on pamphlets, [1], 2-15, [16], [iv], [1], 2-12.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by Johannes Huober (p. i), with marginal annotations in another hand.

binding.p: Contemporary stamped pigskin over wooden boards (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by the Counts of Waldbott-Bassenheim (stamp of G.W.B.D., probably standing for Gräflich von Waldbott-Bassenheim'sche Domanialverwaltung, p. 1).
